Well, when I removed this function:
- mysql_real_escape_string();

it worked well, but I need to validate the data I received from server-side. Any ideas why mysql_real_escape_string() caused this error ?! :)

i think your php code is not executed till the end, mysql_real_escape_string requires that a MySQL connection be opened before calling it (because it uses this connection to get encoding info needed to decide what characters to escape and other stuff)

so, i think calling this function stops php code execution

try this at the very beginning of the page 
<?php
echo '<pre>';
print_r($_GET);
echo '</pre>';
?>

and post back the result
